This paper deals with game theory and decision making, specifically the concept of iterated admissibility. The paper uses mathematical structures and operators to provide a characterization of IA, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.GT (game theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses LPSs and probability structures, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also deals with notions of belief and knowledge, which are relevant to the sub-categories of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and data structures (cs.DS).
